        "type":"SourceInfo",
        "node":{
          "type":"XmlTextNode",
          "contents":"<p>As most files where taken from the examples and from other projects, all DTDs and schemas refer to the project's site, where the default DTD or schema resides. Here comes the problem: For some reason, the JBoss site misses the seam DTDs today (Check <a href=\"http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-1.1.dtd\"rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-1.1.dtd</a>, <a href=\"http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-1.2.dtd\"rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-1.2.dtd</a>, <a href=\"http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-2.0.dtd\"rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.jboss.com/products/seam/components-2.0.dtd</a>). Since the JBoss server validates the XML at bootstrap using this location, the application deployment failed. </p>"
